<br>
10-20 Enchanters, soloing using the charm line versus magicians doing the same. We could select several different areas to test in as well. As far as the measuring stick we'd use, we would have to know the general HP of the mob being soloed to find out if the 50% xp penalty comes into effect. We could set a time limit of say, 2 hours. The side with the most mobs killed (also consider the xp penalty)<br>
<br>
Thing is, can we get the people? Can we rely on their honesty as well? <br>
<br>
I have to admit, I'd certainly like to see this argument put to rest. I'm very curious on the outcome.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umaldisdainatheist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maldisdain Atheist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#333333>(5/30/02 9:02:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=225.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/StaffOfSerpent2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is Charm really overpowering for solo? lets find out?</span><hr size=1> Well... the other thing to consider is the number of deaths that each side has.  And, of course, they wouldn't be allowed to help each other.<br>
<br>
They'd also have to be comparably equipped... and either equally buffed, or unbuffed.  Furthermore, you'd want to be sure they were all the same level or, in the case of level 60+ characters, had very similar AA totals....<br>
<br>
My prediction:<br>
<br>
If both sides have SOW (or JBoots, etc), enchanters will slightly edge out magicians in number of kills, but have 5-10 times as many deaths.<br>
<br>
If SOW is not allowed, enchanters will refuse to participate OR have fewer kills and 10-20 times as many deaths.<br>
-----<br>
<br>
If we're talking Dire Charm here, it will really be zone dependent.<br>
