The whole thing is mob dependant anyway, and the non-pet abilities of the class such as KEI or cadeau come into play too much. If you're talking normal charm as opposed to dire charm, it's really not worth comparing. The whole thing about a charmed pet being stronger, but being able to wail the heck out of you, and oh yeah, take mana every now and then, put summoned pets in a whole different category than charmed pets. Dire charm on the other hand, essentially functions as a mage pet, and would be worth comparing. <p><center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=109465>~~~~Krilen !~~~~</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umaldisdainatheist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maldisdain Atheist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#333333>(5/31/02 3:13:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=225.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/StaffOfSerpent2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is Charm really overpowering for solo? lets find out?</span><hr size=1> Alright... how's this?<br>
