</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uansifiretosser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ansi Firetosser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 269<br> <font color=#333333>(5/31/02 1:12:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=225.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is Charm really overpowering for solo? lets find out?</span><hr size=1> I'm amazed that people really want to run tests to see if a different class is overpowered in one aspect of gameplay.<br>
<br>
To what end?  To say, &quot;See?  Proof that Enchanters have it better than Magicians!&quot;  or to say, &quot;See?  We need better (insert any mage wish) because Enchanters are so much better at us at soloing!&quot;<br>
<br>
If it's simply a scientific curiosity then I suppose the subject of this thread would be better to read, &quot;Is charm really useful for soloing?&quot;  <br>
<br>
See the difference?  One seems positive (or at least neutral) and the other seems negative and has an implicit thread included. (overpowered? Nerf)<br>
<br>
Of course you can do what you wish, and recruit who you wish.  I'm thinking you should recruit over on an Enchanter board though.  Unless again, you hope the results will be able to be used for some sort of ammo against either Enchanters or Verdant in some sort of comparision war.<br>
