<img src="http://crodley.home.mindspring.com/watch.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umaldisdainatheist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maldisdain Atheist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#333333>(5/31/02 4:31:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=225.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/StaffOfSerpent2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hmm.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Odd prediction..<br>
<br>
I think it's zone dependent, but in general the enchanter will outperform the magician due to slow, haste and their crowd control (less wipeouts). <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yeah... running speed buffs are a very important part of regaining control of a formerly-charmed mob.  The problem with comparing regular charm to, well, anything, is that it is incredibly erratic.  On a good run, it takes very little mana to kill your enemies (because, eventually, you want to kill your pet, too)... other times it's... pull with tash... root... charm.  Haste.  Pull with slow to charmed pet.  Root.  /pet attack.  Root breaks.  Root breaks.  Charm breaks.  Attempt to root... resisted... try to stun... resisted... stun... stunned the pet.  Back off... recharm through the slowed mob... root slowed mob... /pet attack.  Rune self.  <br>
<br>
Hundreds and hundreds of mana.  With a run-speed buff in an open area, however, enchanters can often regain control (at the expensive mana cost) <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> without</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> taking a few hundred points of damage.  As the damage builds up, we are forced to rune ourselves more and more (which is extremely mana-intensive... and expensive) and, eventually, hit a threshold where we simply cannot risk another pull (for mana or health reasons)... and often then we still have a pet.  So we have to gate or zone... and come back and regain health and mana.<br>
<br>
That's why runspeed buffs make such a significant difference.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> One thing that's more important than Jboots, SoW, buffs, levels, AA's, etc. of course though is the skill of the player, which is impossible to judge. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I agree completely.<br>
